name: Alex Yee
summary: Olympic triathlon champion Alex Yee has announced his intention to compete in the 2025 London Marathon, marking a significant shift in his athletic career. The decision, described as a "no-brainer" by Yee, follows his success in triathlon, including a memorable gold medal at the Tokyo Olympics. Aiming to achieve a target time of 2 hours and 7 minutes, Yee expressed his eagerness to challenge himself in the marathon distance, viewing it as a natural progression in his athletic journey.

name: Andrew Ridgeley
summary: In recent news, Wham!'s Andrew Ridgeley has reflected on his past and the loss of his bandmate, George Michael. Ridgeley revealed that he has chosen "famous anonymity" by distancing himself from the spotlight. Ridgeley shared that he avoids listening to Wham!'s Christmas hit, "Last Christmas," due to its association with Michael's absence. Despite the pain, he believes "time is a great healer." Ridgeley spoke about the emotional experience of filming a special anniversary show, where the band "felt" Michael's presence. Ridgeley admitted that he never tires of hearing "Last Christmas" and cherishes its legacy. In a documentary, Wham!'s stars shared their memories of Michael. Pepsi & Shirlie discussed the enduring impact of "Last Christmas" at 40 years since its release. Additionally, Ridgeley returned to the Swiss Alps for a BBC documentary about the iconic Christmas song.

name: Mark Cavendish
summary: Sir Mark Cavendish, a retired British cyclist known as the "Manx Missile," has been honored with the BBC Sports Personality of the Year Lifetime Achievement Award. Despite being snubbed from the shortlist for the main award, Cavendish expressed mixed emotions, acknowledging the honor but also stating his competitive desire to be considered for the top prize. The award recognizes his exceptional career, which includes numerous Tour de France stage wins and a world championship title. Additionally, Cavendish has been celebrated with a set of stamps on the Isle of Man and featured in an article detailing his family life. The news also covered his potential departure from the XDS Astana cycling team in 2025, leaving his future in the sport uncertain.
